 shines light on his belief in the importance of giving in the present to make an impact on the future, and on his encouragement of beneficiaries to become partners in community institutions and projects. Rosenwald emerges from the pages as a compassionate man whose generosity and wisdom transformed the practice of philanthropy itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aBusinessmenzUnited StatesvBiography. 0aJewish businesspeoplezUnited StatesvBiography. 0aPhilanthropistszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aBIOGRAPHY & AUTOBIOGRAPHY / Rich & Famous.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311063898140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300231328423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300231328/original  a978-3-11-063898-1  Yale University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles